defaultLikewise our 
defaultFA 
defaultTesco Skills
default coaches are fully trained to deliver to boys and girls. Our FA Tesco Skills primary school programme (5-11 year olds) sees our coaches deliver football physical literacy sessions in schools to pupils and provide tailored support for teachers to train them
default to deliver such programmes in the future. This age group is so important 
defaultbecause,
default if youngsters can be taught well and master basic physical literacy skills
default,
default they are more likely to approach physical education with enthusiasm in secondary school and devel
defaultop a sporting habit for life. The FA Tesco Skills programme has, since its creation in 2007, supported over 21,500 teachers in 7,500 schools and provided 4.5m places to children- 57% boys and 43% girls. The 
defaultin-curriculum 
defaultprogramme is free for schools. 
