defaultBefore 1993 the Women’s Football Association (WFA) was responsible for the women’s game. The WFA was as an independent body in 1969 and was not part of The FA. 
defaultIt focussed on the then fledgling international competitions and even took an England side to th
defaulte finals of the European Championship in 1984. However, they were unable to develop the game at grassroots level due to limited funding.
